	(9,1,'2016-10-16 19:19:50','2016-10-16 19:19:50','I have lived in Duluth all my life, and I love it! I am an active person who loves hiking, bicycling, and swimming in the big lake. I just recently returned from a longer backpacking trip on the Superior Hiking Trail, hiking from Two Harbors to my home here in Duluth. What a journey! I am happily married (3 years!) and love spending time with my family, which includes two wonderful step-children. Both my husband and I are active with the local theater scene, and I also teach and take dance classes. I believe my interest in many things athletic allows me to relate that much more with my clientele, experiencing firsthand what gets sore in certain activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Training:</strong>   I am a 2013 honors graduate of Lake Superior College. Certified in Relaxation, Deep Tissue, Sports, Pregnancy, Lymphatic, Geriatric, Rotator Cuff Protocol, and Craniosacral Levels 1 &amp; 2.\r\n\r\n<strong>My style:</strong>  I have a very intutitive approach. I love working with each client and their individual goals to create a personalized session each time. I have a very rhythmic flow, and have consistent pressure that can vary between gentle to very firm, based on each client\'s individual needs. I am honored to provide a relaxing, safe, therapeutic space that is free of judgement. All are welcome.','About','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2016-10-16 19:20:00','2016-10-16 19:20:00','',0,'http://nisi.dev/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),
	(10,1,'2016-10-16 19:19:50','2016-10-16 19:19:50','','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2016-10-16 19:19:50','2016-10-16 19:19:50','',9,'http://nisi.dev/2016/10/16/9-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
