	(48,1,'2016-11-08 21:01:00','2016-11-08 21:01:00','Created by Peggy Lamb, LMT, this service works specifically with the muscles of your rotator cuff in the shoulder girdle. This is a more interactive therapy, working with passive movement (I move you), active movement (you move yourself), and resistance (through a weight or counteracting pressure) to encourage a stuck or frozen muscle to release. This is applicable to people who are experiencing shoulder pain, discomfort, reduced range of motion, frozen shoulder syndrome, or for anyone who simply works at a computer for long hours and wants to incorporate this technique into their session.','Rotator Cuff Protocol','','publish','closed','closed','','rotator-cuff-protocol','','','2016-11-08 21:01:00','2016-11-08 21:01:00','',0,'http://nisi.dev/?post_type=ns_service&#038;p=48',0,'ns_service','',0),
